726063f-a.text:
Astoria Boulevard (cobblestones thereon), at the S. E. corner of 1st Street, showing the former Wilson Hotel; kept by Captain Tinker in 1841; Captain A. Horner, prior to 1859 and subsequently by one Wilson.

1922

Eugene L. Arabruster Collection

726062f-b.text:
Astoria Boulevard, at First Street, on the East River, showing the ferry house of the municipal ferry operating to 92nd Street, Manhattan. View 2 shows the old slips, which were replaced by new Ones a few years later. Seen through one of the slips is the old Wilson Hotel.
P. L. Sperr  March 9, 1931
NO REPRODUCTIONS  Views 1,2

724950f-a.text:
1st Street, at, and adjoining the S. E. corner of Astoria Boulevard. The corner house, which is boarded up, is the Village Regular Democratic Club, according to P. L. Sperr. It is a frame house, and the one contiguous to it is made of brick.
